
Beam super-shield damage

When a super-shield is damaged is controlled by BeamWeapon::OnUpdate, which
sets bDamageSuperShield to true when it's possible to damage a layer of super-shield.

This enables super-shield damage when the beam reaches 33% of it's travel,
and again when it reaches 80%. The second time only applies if the beam
is more than 20 pixels long (NOT greater than or equal to, which matters
for the level-1 beam drone).
